[h1]final[/h1]

Use the [b]final [/b]keyword to mark a variable constant, so that it can be assigned only once.
[b]Example:[/b][code format="java" codeId="771"]class MyClass {
  public static [b]final [/b]double PI = 3.14; 
  public static void main(String[ ] args) {
    System.out.println(PI);
  }
}[/code]
[b]PI [/b]is now a constant. Any attempt to assign it a value will cause an error.
[note]Methods and classes can also be marked [b]final[/b]. This serves to restrict methods so that they can't be overridden and classes so that they can't be made subclasses. 
These concepts will be covered in the next module.[/note]
